  <!-- Section: Application Process -->
  <section id="application" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Application Process</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Cyprus offers flexibility in the application process—you can apply from a Cypriot consulate abroad or in-person in Cyprus after entering legally (e.g., on a tourist visa or visa-free entry). Processing typically takes 5-7 weeks.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={timelineColumns} rows={timelineRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Step-by-Step Guide</h3>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">1</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Gather and Prepare Documents</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Collect all required documents: employment contract or freelance contracts (1+ year duration), proof of income, criminal record certificates, and accommodation proof. Get apostilles and translations into English or Greek.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">2</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Secure Health Insurance</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Purchase comprehensive international health insurance covering your planned stay in Cyprus. Obtain an official certificate confirming coverage dates, amounts, and Cyprus as covered territory.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">3</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Choose Application Method</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Decide whether to apply at a Cypriot consulate in your home country or travel to Cyprus first (visa-free or on tourist visa) and apply at the Civil Registry and Migration Department in person.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">4</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Submit Application</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Submit your completed application with all supporting documents and pay the €70 application fee. If applying in Cyprus, you'll submit to the Civil Registry and Migration Department.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">5</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Wait for Processing</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Processing typically takes 5-7 weeks. The authorities may request additional documents or clarification. Track your application status through the Civil Registry's system or your consulate.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">6</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Receive Approval</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Once approved, you'll receive notification. If you applied abroad, you can now travel to Cyprus. If you applied in-country, proceed to the next step.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">7</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Apply for Alien Registration Certificate</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Within 7 days of arrival (or approval if already in Cyprus), apply for your ARC at the Civil Registry. Bring original documents, photos, and the €70 ARC fee. Biometrics will be collected.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">8</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Receive Residence Card</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">After 2-4 weeks, collect your ARC. This card is valid for 1 year and can be renewed for up to 2 additional years (3 years total). Keep it with you as proof of legal residence.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>In-country application tip:</strong> Many applicants find it easier to visit Cyprus first (visa-free for many nationalities), find accommodation, then apply in person. This allows you to explore before committing and speeds up the process since you're already on-site.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

