  <!-- Section: Common Mistakes -->
  <section id="mistakes" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Underestimating the Income Threshold</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">The €3,500/month is net income, after taxes and deductions in your home country. Some applicants miscalculate and fall short. If you have family, remember to add +20% for spouse and +15% per child. A family of four needs €5,250/month minimum.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Applying When Quota is Nearly Full</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Cyprus limits DNV permits to 1,000 total. While quotas can be expanded (as in March 2025), applying late in the year risks delays or rejection if the cap is reached. Apply early in the calendar year when quotas reset.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Short-Term Contracts</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Your employment or freelance contract must show at least 1 year duration. Month-to-month arrangements or short-term projects may not satisfy requirements. Aggregate multiple contracts or get a longer-term agreement from your main client.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Assuming Schengen Access</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Cyprus is an EU member but NOT in the Schengen Zone. Your Cyprus DNV doesn't grant Schengen travel rights. You'll still be limited by your passport's Schengen allowance (typically 90/180 days) or need separate visas for Schengen countries.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Missing the 7-Day ARC Deadline</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">After your DNV is approved and you're in Cyprus, you must apply for the Alien Registration Certificate within 7 days. Missing this deadline can complicate your stay and future renewals. Mark the date and have documents ready.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

